## 6. Session Prompts — Deep Review

**All 10 session prompts reviewed structurally. Rating: 9/10.**

### Format Consistency ✅
Every prompt has the same structure:
- Context Briefing (why this day matters)
- Active Plan Reference (which files to attach)
- Fixes to Apply Today (table with Fix ID + Severity + Action)
- Tasks In Order (morning/afternoon/evening breakdown)
- Expected Deliverable / Success Criteria (checkboxes)
- Skills to Attach
- (Major days) Critical Reminders ⚠️

### Highlights by Day

| Day | Standout Feature | Risk |
|-----|-----------------|------|
| **Day 1** | Includes inline `BusinessConstants.java` code — AI doesn't need to guess the values | 9 migrations is aggressive for a first day. 2 hours of "Designing Data-Intensive Applications reading" during an 8-hour implementation day risks schedule pressure |
| **Day 5** | Correctly includes the Lua script inline — no ambiguity on what "atomic" means | The concurrent test (10 threads, 5 available) is simpler than Fix 16.1's test (100 threads, 50 available). Ensure Day 5's simpler test doesn't create false confidence |
| **Day 8** | Best prompt in the set. Fix 11.1 is correctly pulled forward from Day 11 to Day 8. The 10-step `reserveTickets()` outline is clear | `BookingState.AVAILABLE` is listed as a state in the enum on line 47 but Fix 11.2 recommends removing it. This should be resolved before Day 8 runs |
| **Day 9** | The webhook architecture diagram (inline code) is clear and correct | `StripeConfig` uses `@PostConstruct` to set `Stripe.apiKey` globally — this is correct but note that the Stripe SDK global is not thread-safe if `Stripe.apiKey` is ever mutated after startup. Safe as written, just document the assumption |

### Cross-Prompt Issue — Day Count vs. Session Count
The workflow says Days 1–21 (21 days, 105–122 hours) but only 10 session prompts exist for days 1–10. Days 11–21 have no session prompts.

> [!IMPORTANT]
> Days 11–21 have no session prompt files. This is a planning gap. Sessions for Days 11+ will need to be run without pre-written prompts, making them more vulnerable to context loss and deviation from the plan.

**Recommendation:** Create session prompts for Days 11–21. At minimum create stubs with the fix table for each day.

