## 7. `.github/` Configuration — Deep Review

### `copilot-instructions.md` — Rating: 10/10
This is one of the most comprehensive Copilot instruction files I've seen. It covers:
- All architecture decisions with "why" rationale
- Full package naming convention (exact, no deviations)
- Every `BusinessConstants` value pre-defined in a table
- Critical components flagged (`DistributedLockService`, `BookingStateMachineConfig`, `InventoryService`, `StripeWebhookController`)
- Logging standards (SLF4J only, parameterized)
- Testing standards (naming convention, Testcontainers, 100-thread concurrency test required)

**One issue:** The instructions reference `private static final Logger logger = LoggerFactory.getLogger(MyClass.class)` but the project uses Lombok `@Slf4j` annotation which is simpler and less error-prone. The skill file and instructions should agree on which style to use.

### `instructions/` — 9 Files Present ✅
All expected instruction files exist:
- `springboot.instructions.md` — Spring Boot practices
- `security-and-owasp.instructions.md` — OWASP
- `spec-driven-workflow-v1.instructions.md` — SpecKit workflow
- `object-calisthenics.instructions.md` — Code quality rules
- `oop-design-patterns.instructions.md` — Design patterns
- `self-explanatory-code-commenting.instructions.md` — Commenting standards
- `update-docs-on-code-change.instructions.md` — Doc freshness
- `performance-optimization.instructions.md` — Perf patterns
- `nextjs.instructions.md` — Frontend

**Note:** The `spec-driven-workflow-v1.instructions.md` file at 12KB is the most important of these for session workflow. Verify its `applyTo` glob covers `*.md` files so it auto-injects during plan and tasks phases.

### `agents/` — 9 SpecKit Agents Present ✅
All 9 agents present: `analyze`, `plan`, `tasks`, `implement`, `checklist`, `clarify`, `constitution`, `specify`, `taskstoissues`. 

The `speckit.taskstoissues` agent (1KB — very small) may be undersized for what it needs to do. Confirm it can push tasks to GitHub Issues if needed for tracking.

