## 10. Concurrency & Correctness Analysis

The fixes collectively address an impressive range of distributed systems correctness problems. Here's an independent validation:

| Scenario | Protection Mechanism | Status |
|----------|---------------------|--------|
| Two users race on last seat | Redis Lua floor guard (Fix 5.1) + TOCTOU double-check inside lock (Fix 8.1) | ✅ Correct — two layers |
| Same user double-clicks Reserve | User-scoped lock key `tier:{tierId}:user:{userId}` | ✅ Correct |
| Stripe delivers same webhook twice simultaneously | DB UNIQUE constraint + `DataIntegrityViolationException` catch (Fix 9.2) | ✅ Correct — only DB constraint survives race |
| App crashes after 200 sent but before DB commit | Impossible — 200 only sent after service method returns (Fix 9.1) | ✅ Correct |
| Multi-instance scheduler runs expiry job twice | Distributed lock on `scheduler:reservation-expiry` (Fix 8.3) | ✅ Correct |
| Redis cache cold on startup | `InventoryWarmupHealthIndicator` blocks readiness (Fix 5.2) | ✅ Correct — but Railway health check path must be `/actuator/health/readiness` |
| Optimistic lock collision under load | `@Retryable` with 3 attempts + exponential backoff (Fix 8.4) | ✅ Correct |
| Refund denied with no user notification | `NotifyRefundDeniedAction` + `RefundDeniedEvent` to RabbitMQ (Fix 10.1) | ✅ Correct |
| 50 QR codes blocking webhook thread | Async `ticket.generation.queue` (Fix 10.2) | ✅ Correct |
| Organizer marks their own ticket attended | `CheckInGuard` at state machine layer (Fix 8.2) | ✅ Correct |
| Multi-replica distributed pricing/expiry | No fix exists yet for `PricingEngineService` if it has time-sensitive calculations | ⚠️ Unaddressed |

**One unaddressed scenario:** If dynamic pricing is calculated on all instances simultaneously, there's no distributed coordination for the `80% threshold triggers 25% surge` logic. This may cause inconsistent pricing for ~1 second during surge onset. Acceptable for Phase 1A but worth noting for Phase 1B.

